Meet Kinley! She’s 13 years old and currently battling cancer! When we talked she shared with me how it took a toll on her self confidence when she attends school because she lost all of her hair due to chemotherapy. 
She said “Trenton it has been my dream to get a wig done by you” “I would love a dirty blonde color the same length as my hair was”. “Is it possible?” 
As soon as she said that I immediately knew what to create for her! 
When she saw her hair when she turned around she had the biggest smile and said “I love it” “This means everything to me”. She then proceeded to show full energy and excitement! 
Giving her this crown of confidence was everything…I’m so thankful I was able to do this for you Kinley!
Stay strong…you got this 🤍

I never do this…I want to be transparent with my supporters and show you all that my life isn’t perfect!When life tries to knock you down…put god first…stand up and keep going! Nothing is perfect, no one’s life! For anyone out there that’s going through it I understand!

All the supportive comments & messages, prayers, the stories some of you all shared with me made me realize I needed to connect with my supporters on another level. You all helped me through a time that was tough and gave me words of encouragement! I will forever be appreciative for you all’s support last night and for everyone following my journey! I can’t wait to share the exciting things that are coming up…It’s winning season for everybody! Put God first…And hold the people close to you that love and support you!
